        <body>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">32 G</hi>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>, <date>May 6, 1857</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>, <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear friend:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I don't know whether you can use the enclosed article<lb/> and I am
                not hurt in the least, if you tell me it is not suit-<lb/>able. I feel that I have
                not looked around with a sufficiently<lb/> searching mind, to make a complete and
                correct report. But I<lb/> believe that I have told the truth. Should you decide to
                print<lb/> it, then I wish you would correct my bad English. Although I<lb/>
                generally do not do it, but in this case you may be at liberty<lb/> to add or leave
                off as you see fit, for I can readily see the<lb/> lack of better comprehension. I
                should have added that for the<lb/> first time I preached here in the German
                language on <date>Rosh Hashonah</date>.<lb/> The congregation might have gotten some
                new members. The Bavarian<lb/> congregation followed this example at once. But I
                don't want to<lb/> talk about myself nor do I wish to go into details.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In the near future I hope to send you an entirely<lb/> different
                contribution, which might have more value.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am happy, exceedingly happy that you continue<lb/> the Occident
                and am only sorry that I cannot do anything to further<lb/> its distribution.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">When you come to <placeName>New York</placeName> I want you to see
                my Sefarin<lb/> Especially, ask for my Pehad Yitzhak, the great and rare
                talmudic<lb/> REAL (ANAL.) LEXICON (dictionary). Only a few copies are in<lb/>
                existence and none are sold in book stores. <persName>Dr. Zunz</persName>,
                    <persName>Sachs</persName> and<lb/>
                <persName>Rappaport</persName> paid $30. for a copy. It will greatly assist you
                in<lb/> your work and you get 50% off the list price. You need not spend<lb/> a cent
                and I can in this manner not only pay off my debt, but also<lb/> the $3. for the new
                subscription of the Occident. And moreover, I<lb/> would consider it a favor for
                which I promise to be thankful in<lb/> later years when I, God helping, will find
                myself in better financial<lb/> circumstances.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours very truly,</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">ISIDOR BUSH</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Addressed: <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>, Editor of the Occident,
                    <placeName>Philadelphia, Pa.</placeName></p>
        </body>
